Entitlements: Terms to Know

Learn useful terms related to entitlement features in Salesforce.

A unit of customer support in Salesforce, such as “phone support” or “web support.”

An association between a contact and an entitlement, for example, a named caller. Contacts on an account don’t automatically inherit the account’s entitlements.

Predefined terms of customer support that can be quickly added to products in Salesforce.

A collection of Salesforce features that help you provide the correct service levels to your customers. It includes:

* Entitlements
* Entitlement processes
* Service contracts
* Experience access to entitlements
* Reporting on entitlement management

A customer support agreement between you and your customers. Service contracts can represent warranties, subscriptions, service level agreements (SLAs), and other types of customer support.

Specific products covered by a service contract.

A timeline that includes all the steps (milestones) that support agents must complete to resolve a support record.

A required step in an entitlement process. Examples include First Response and Resolution Time on cases.

A time-dependent workflow action that occurs on a milestone in an entitlement process, such as sending an email alert or updating fields on a case.
title: Understanding Entitlements in Service Cloud
